1. Use the ssh command to log in to serverx as the student user. Switch to root on serverx using redhat as the password.
2. Create a directory called /home/techdocs.
3. Change the group ownership of the /home/techdocs directory to the techdocs group.
4. Verify that users in the techdocs group can create and edit files in the /home/techdocs
directory.
5. Set permissions on the /home/techdocs directory. On the /home/techdocs directory, read/write/execute permissions (7) for the owner/user and group, and no permissions (0) for other users.
6. Verify that the permissions are set properly.





On serverx, start the psacct service.
1 install mariadb-server pakcage
2. Configure the mariadb service to start at system boot.
3. Stop the rsyslog service.
4. Configure the rsyslog service so that it does not start at system boot.
5. Reboot serverb before evaluating the lab.




On serverx, ensure that newly created users have passwords that must be changed every 30 days.
1. Create the new group called consultants with a GID of 35000.
2. Create the consultant1, consultant2, and consultant3 users with consultants as their supplementary group.
3. Set the consultant1, consultant2, and consultant3 accounts to expire in 90 days from the current day.
4. Change the password policy for the consultant2 account to require a new password every 15 days.

